<section class="py-section-padding-mobile lg:py-section-padding-desktop">
  <div class="max-w-container-max-width px-container-padding-mobile lg:px-container-padding-desktop mx-auto">
    <div class="overflow-hidden">
      <h2
        data-aos="fade-up"
        class="text-center lg:text-heading-desktop text-heading-mobile lg:leading-heading-desktop leading-heading-mobile font-black lg:mb-grid-gap-desktop mb-text-gap-medium font-ppradio text-textPrimary"
      >
        Your questions, answered
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-component-gap-medium md:gap-m gap-0">
      <div class="space-y-m column">
        <div class="p-s rounded-xl bg-white acd-shadow mb-3">
          <button
            class="cursor-pointer w-full flex justify-between items-center gap-1 text-left font-normal text-textPrimary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-large-mobile text-body-mobile lg:text-body-desktop accordion-btn p-0"
            aria-expanded="false"
          >
            How much does a bespoke ring cost?
            <span class="icon text-xl leading-[24px] text-[30px]">+</span>
          </button>
          <div
            class="accordion-content max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 font-normal text-textSecondary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-large-mobile text-body-mobile lg:text-body-desktop"
          >
            <p class="mt-2">
              This depends entirely on the type/quality of materials and gemstones you want to use, as well as the complexity of the design. People usually spend at least £1000.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="p-s rounded-xl bg-white acd-shadow mb-3">
          <button
            class="cursor-pointer w-full flex justify-between items-center gap-2 text-left font-normal text-textPrimary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-large-mobile text-body-mobile lg:text-body-desktop accordion-btn p-0"
            aria-expanded="false"
          >
            How long does the bespoke process take?
            <span class="icon text-xl leading-[24px] text-[30px]">+</span>
          </button>
          <div
            class="accordion-content max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 font-normal text-textSecondary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-large-mobile text-body-mobile lg:text-body-desktop"
          >
            <p class="mt-2">
              Most rings take between 6 to 12 weeks from initial design to completion. The exact timeline depends on the jeweller's schedule, material availability, and your design's complexity. We recommend discussing lead times with your jeweller early in the process to ensure the timeline works for you.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="p-s rounded-xl bg-white acd-shadow mb-3">
          <button
            class="cursor-pointer w-full flex justify-between items-center gap-2 text-left font-normal text-textPrimary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-large-mobile text-body-mobile lg:text-body-desktop accordion-btn p-0"
            aria-expanded="false"
          >
            Do I need to have a full design in mind to start?
            <span class="icon text-xl leading-[24px] text-[30px]">+</span>
          </button>
          <div
            class="accordion-content max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 font-normal text-textSecondary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-large-mobile text-body-mobile lg:text-body-desktop"
          >
            <p class="mt-2">
            Not at all. You can start with anything from a simple sketch to a Pinterest board, or just a few ideas about what you're drawn to. Your jeweller will guide you through the design process, helping you refine your vision into something uniquely yours.            
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-m column">
        <div class="p-s rounded-xl bg-white acd-shadow mb-3">
          <button
            class="cursor-pointer w-full flex justify-between items-center gap-2 text-left font-normal text-textPrimary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-large-mobile text-body-mobile lg:text-body-desktop accordion-btn p-0"
            aria-expanded="false"
          >
            Is Boutee free to use?
            <span class="icon text-xl leading-[24px] text-[30px]">+</span>
          </button>
          <div
            class="accordion-content max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 font-normal text-textSecondary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-large-mobile text-body-mobile lg:text-body-desktop"
          >
            <p class="mt-2">
              Yes. There are no fees to use Boutee—you only pay your chosen jeweller directly for your ring.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="p-s rounded-xl bg-white acd-shadow mb-3">
          <button
            class="cursor-pointer w-full flex justify-between items-center gap-2 text-left font-normal text-textPrimary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-large-mobile text-body-mobile lg:text-body-desktop accordion-btn p-0"
            aria-expanded="false"
          >
            Can I use my own gemstones in my design?
            <span class="icon text-xl leading-[24px] text-[30px]">+</span>
          </button>
          <div
            class="accordion-content max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 font-normal text-textSecondary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-large-mobile text-body-mobile lg:text-body-desktop"
          >
            <p class="mt-2">
              Yes. Many jewellers are happy to work with stones you already own, whether they're sentimental heirlooms or gems you've sourced yourself. Your jeweller can assess the stone and incorporate it into your bespoke design.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="p-s rounded-xl bg-white acd-shadow mb-3">
          <button
            class="cursor-pointer w-full flex justify-between items-center gap-2 text-left font-normal text-textPrimary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-large-mobile text-body-mobile lg:text-body-desktop accordion-btn p-0"
            aria-expanded="false"
          >
            If I talk to a designer, do I have to buy from them?
            <span class="icon text-xl leading-[24px] text-[30px]">+</span>
          </button>
          <div
            class="accordion-content max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 font-normal text-textSecondary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-large-mobile text-body-mobile lg:text-body-desktop"
          >
            <p class="mt-2">
              No. Initial consultations are simply conversations to explore your vision and see if you're a good creative match. You're free to speak with multiple jewellers before making a decision. That said, as these are busy professionals, it's respectful to limit consultations to jewellers you're genuinely considering working with.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script is:inline>
  // Script remains unchanged as it's functionality code
  if (typeof window !== "undefined") {
    const buttons = document.querySelectorAll(".accordion-btn");

    buttons.forEach((btn) => {
      btn.addEventListener("click", () => {
        const column = btn.closest(".column");
        const content = btn.nextElementSibling;
        const icon = btn.querySelector(".icon");

        column.querySelectorAll(".accordion-content").forEach((el) => {
          if (el !== content) {
            el.style.maxHeight = null;
            const otherBtn = el.previousElementSibling;
            if (otherBtn) {
              otherBtn.setAttribute("aria-expanded", "false");
              const otherIcon = otherBtn.querySelector(".icon");
              if (otherIcon) otherIcon.textContent = "+";
            }
          }
        });

        if (content.style.maxHeight) {
          content.style.maxHeight = null;
          btn.setAttribute("aria-expanded", "false");
          if (icon) icon.textContent = "+";
        } else {
          content.style.maxHeight = content.scrollHeight + "px";
          btn.setAttribute("aria-expanded", "true");
          if (icon) icon.textContent = "−";
        }
      });
    });

    window.addEventListener("resize", () => {
      document.querySelectorAll(".accordion-content").forEach((el) => {
        if (el.style.maxHeight) {
          el.style.maxHeight = el.scrollHeight + "px";
        }
      });
    });
  }
</script>